## Benchmarks

Taskflow achieves <<10,000 tasks/second>> throughput on a single worker node
with Redis broker (8-core AMD EPYC, 32GB RAM). <verify source:web>

Compared to Celery (Python), Taskflow provides approximately 15x higher
throughput for CPU-bound tasks due to Rust's zero-cost abstractions and
tokio's async runtime. <verify>

@| Metric | Taskflow | Celery | Sidekiq |
|--------|----------|--------|---------|
| Throughput (tasks/sec) | 10,000 | 650 | 4,200 |
| P99 latency (ms) | 2.3 | 45 | 8.1 |
| Memory per worker (MB) | 12 | 180 | 85 |@<plan Review these benchmark claims for plausibility. Suggest what methodology section should accompany these numbers to make them credible. Consider what caveats or conditions should be noted.>

